<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="1417" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1417">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1317</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The</hi>
                            <gloss type="from">
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                            <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MGT1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Marye</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-30">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 30, 1914</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>127. German Embassy informs Department safe-conducts taken from Germans
                            captured on Persian territory by Russians at RussoPersian border, male
                            German prisoners made spend nine days in jail with highwaymen at
                            Nakhichevan. The male Germans found Tabriz sent to Astrakhan prisoners
                            of war.</p>
                        <p>Bring to attention Foreign Office and do what you properly can behalf
                            Germans imprisoned.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>